== Description == [[File:HistoryFruit03.png|thumb|Mossy overgrowth in a castle.]] '''The History of Fruit''' is a nine-level episode for Heretic. Despite the silliness of the title, story and map names, and the presence in two levels of a ugly "billboard" texture advertising the mod, this is not a {{dw|joke_WAD|jokewad}}. The maps are well-crafted, with beautiful architecture and challenging gameplay. The map set was primarily designed for co-op, though it is still perfectly playable in single-player mode.
== External links == * [http://www.realm667.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=1031&pop=1&page=20&Itemid=152 Medieval Textures] used to supplement the stock Heretic textures.
